.TH "ABSTRACTRANGE.ENDCONTAINER" "3JS" "January 24, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
AbstractRange.endContainer \- AbstractRange: endContainer property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The read\-only \f[B]\f[CB]endContainer\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]AbstractRange\f[R] interface returns the \f[CR]Node\f[R] in which
the end of the range is located.
.PP
To change the end position, use the \f[CR]Range.setEnd()\f[R] method or
a similar one.
.SH VALUE
The \f[CR]Node\f[R] which contains the last character of the range.
.SH EXAMPLE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] range = document.createRange();
range.setStart(startNode, startOffset);
range.setEnd(endNode, endOffset);

\f[B]const\f[R] endRangeNode = range.endContainer;
.EE
